article.headline: Bowling Green 81, Lamar 68
article.story: HONOLULU (AP) -- John Reimold set four career records, including a career-high 30 points, to lead Bowling Green past Lamar 81-68 in the seventh place game of the Rainbow Classic. Reimold also set career bests in field goals made (11), field goals attempted (20) and 3-point field goals made with seven. Ronald Lewis added 22 points and Steven Wright scored 13 as the Falcons defeated just their second Division I opponent of the season to improve to 4-7. Teddy Davis scored 21 points to lead Lamar (6-6) and Blake Whittle added in a career high 16 as the Cardinals dropped their fifth straight game. After closing to 58-57 with 8:46 remaining in the second half, the Cardinals turned the ball over four times while the Falcons went on a 15-3 run over the next five and a half minutes. Bowling Green shot 47 percent from the field (27-of-57) while forcing 15 turnovers. The Falcons turned the ball over 17 times.
